It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, and SVHN. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with defending against attacks on machine learning models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of AI techniques to defend against adversarial attacks. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques to defend against adversarial attacks.
